@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Kaleido" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries a
are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must have at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  The game play is very simple: Everytime you click on a tile (except on the
leftmost or uppermost ones) 4 tiles rotate in a clockwise manner, these tiles
are the tile located on the upper left on the board, the tile located on the
upper row in the same column from where you clicked, the leftmost tile on the
same row you clicked and of course, the tile you clicked. Here's an example:

   a..b            c..a
   ....     -=>    ....
   ....            ....
   c..d            d..b         
      ^
      ^
      Tile clicked

  Note: the spaces marked by a "." are ignored in this example.

  Continue to move the tiles until the original pattern is recreated. When
you finish a game level, Kaleido displays a new pattern, and so on until
you finish level 50, where the game starts again at level 1.

  Try to match each of the 50 game patterns in the least amount of moves
possible...

  You can choose to play the game boards in the normal or in a random
order, by clicking on the "@{b}Normal/Random order@{ub}" button.

  Have fun!

